# Build And Deploy

- When asked to compile, build, deploy, or verify source-code changes on the PiKVM, run `./go.sh`.
- `./go.sh` is the canonical path: it runs the frontend build and deploys the resulting bundle to the PiKVM extra path.
- Do not run `npm run build` as the final verification for deployed app changes unless the user only wants a local build.
- Use `./go.sh --deploy` only when an explicit deploy subcommand is clearer; it is equivalent to `./go.sh`.
